quity stake in Network", "bbox": [143.8, 1082.4, 1030.2, 1103.2]}, {"text": "Solutions. During 2005, VeriSign recognized a gain of $8.2 million on the sale of an equity investment that was", "bbox": [143.8, 1107.4, 1077.8, 1128.2]}, {"text": "previously impaired. During 2004, VeriSign sold 18,000 ordinary shares of its Tokyo-based, majority owned", "bbox": [143.8, 1132.4, 1053.4, 1153.2]}, {"text": "consolidated subsidiary, VeriSign Japan K.K., representing a gain of approximately $74.9 million related to the", "bbox": [143.8, 1157.4, 1074.4, 1178.2]}, {"text": "sale. Other, net primarily consists of foreign exchange rate gains and losses and in 2005 it includes", "bbox": [143.8, 1182.4, 968.4, 1203.2]}, {"text": "approximately $6.0 million of other income related to a litigation settlement with a telecommunication carrier.", "bbox": [143.8, 1207.4, 1066.3, 1228.2]}, {"text": "Note 19.", "bbox": [143.8, 1269.7, 216.8, 1290.5]}, {"text": "Subsequent Events", "bbox": [237.6, 1269.7, 406.1, 1290.5]}, {"text": "In January 2007, VeriSign initiated a restructuring plan to execute a company-wide reorganization replacing", "bbox": [185.5, 1307.4, 1089.9, 1328.3]}, {"text": "the previous business unit structure with a new combined worldwide sales and services team, and an integrated", "bbox": [143.8, 1332.4, 1070.7, 1353.3]}, {"text": "development and products organization. The restructuring plan included workforce reductions, abandonment of", "bbox": [143.8, 1357.4, 1075.5, 1378.3]}, {"text": "excess facilities, disposals of property and equipment, and other charges. In the first quarter of 2007, VeriSign", "bbox": [143.8, 1382.4, 1064.7, 1403.3]}, {"text": "recorded approximately $26.9 million in restructuring charges.", "bbox": [143.8, 1407.5, 668.1, 1428.3]}, {"text": "Ĺ  Form 10-K", "bbox": [1173.9, 362.4, 1199.6, 506.3]}, {"text": "235", "bbox": [603.4, 1465.8, 634.6, 1486.6]}]}